| **Docs-and-rules-only** | **`12-documentation-style`** when editing root or `docs/*.md` prose; light **`09-security-baseline`** (no secrets in examples) | **Skip:** **`01`–`07`**, **`10`**, **`11`**, **`13`**, **`14`**, **`15`** — by definition the diff is only **`.md`** files and **`.cursor/rules/**/*.mdc`**, so no Go or `web/src` paths changed. **Verification:** none of `go vet`, `go test`, `npm test`, or `npm run build`. |
| **Frontend then backend** (explicit user order) | **`10`**, **`09-local`**, **`09-security`**, then **`01` → `07`**, **`11`**, **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`** / **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`** if the matching stack changed, **`09`** | Same verification step at the end |
| **Backend / Go only** | **`01` → `07`**, **`11`**, **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`** (tasks API / store), **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`** (when changing `pkgs/repo` or `/repo` handlers), **`15-database-schema`** when schema-related Go changes, **`09`** | **`10-web-ui`** unless `web/` was touched |
| **Frontend / `web/` only** | **`10`**, **`09-local-verification`** (and **`09-security`** for secrets in client config) | Deep **`01`–`07`** / **`11`** on Go only if Go files changed |
| **Audit / review, no commit** | Read and fix per rules; **do not** run **`08`** | Say explicitly: “audit-only; no commit.” |

## Phases

1. **Orient** — Skim **`AGENTS.md`** (repo map, commands). List **`.cursor/rules/`**, sort by numeric prefix, skip **`00-*`** when *applying* (this file is the playbook, not a style rule).
2. **Test-first (when implementing or fixing behavior)** — Follow **`06-testing.mdc`** (Go) and **`10-web-ui.mdc`** (`web/`): **red** (failing test) → **green** (minimal fix) → **refactor**. Skip for **docs-and-rules-only** and for purely non-behavior edits (see **`06-testing.mdc`** table).
3. **Substantive rules** — In order **`01` → `07`**, then **`11-api-contracts`** (read the checklist when changing HTTP/SSE/JSON boundaries; on a full pass, skim to avoid drift), then **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`** when changing the tasks stack (routes, store, domain, audit/SSE, or task UI that hits the API; skip for trivial fixes), then **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`** when changing the workspace repo slice (`pkgs/repo`, `/repo/*`, `web/src/api/repo.ts`, mention extensions, or `REPO_ROOT` docs; skip for trivial fixes), then **`15-database-schema`** when changing GORM models, `pkgs/tasks/postgres`, SQLite test schema, or `cmd/dbcheck` migrate behavior. Then **`09-security-baseline`** (light scan: secrets, unsafe logs), then **`09-local-verification`** (reminder: **`gofmt`**, **`go vet`**, tests), then **`10`** when `web/` is in scope. When editing root or `docs/*.md` prose, also apply **`12-documentation-style`**. For each: read → inspect → fix → run **targeted** tests for what you changed (do not run the full bar after every single edit). **`99-repo-primer`** is always-on context only, not a separate pass step. **Docs-and-rules-only** scope: skip **`01`–`07`**, **`10`**, **`11`**, **`13`**, **`14`**, **`15`**; run **`12`** (when editing root or `docs/*.md` prose) and light **`09-security-baseline`** only.
4. **Verify** — Once fixes for this pass are done:
   - **Docs-and-rules-only** scope: **no** `go vet`, `go test`, or `web/` npm steps (confirm every path is `.md` or `.cursor/rules/**/*.mdc`).
   - **Otherwise** run the **full bar** once: **`scripts/check.ps1`** (Windows) or **`scripts/check.sh`** (Unix) from repo root, **or** the equivalent: **`gofmt`** check / **`go fmt`**, **`go vet ./...`**, **`go test ./... -count=1`**, and (if `web/` changed) **`npm test`** + **`npm run build`** in **`web/`** (see **`09-local-verification.mdc`**).
   - **Recommended:** for meaningful behavior changes under **`pkgs/`** / **`internal/`**, run scoped coverage per **`06-testing.mdc`** and close obvious gaps (or note why not).
5. **Publish (rule `08`)** — Only if there are changes to commit **and** the user did not ask for audit-only:
   - Apply **`08-atomic-commits`**: atomic commits, then **`git push`** (or set upstream), unless push is impossible—report outcome.
6. **Nothing to do** — If the tree is clean and no rule required edits, say so briefly (no fake commits).

## Constraints

- Do not skip substantive rules unless **clearly not applicable** to the chosen scope.
- Do not move on with **failing** verification (`go vet`, `go test`, or `web/` build when in scope).
- **Batch commits at the end** of the pass per **`08`**; do not mix unrelated concerns in one commit.
- **Contradiction guard:** “Do not commit before the end” means **do not commit mid-pass** while applying substantive rules (**`01`–`07`**, **`11`**, **`13-tasks-stack-extensibility`**, **`14-repo-workspace-extensibility`**, **`15-database-schema`**, **`09`**, **`10`**, **`12`** as applicable); the **end** of the pass is after verification, when **`08`** applies—unless the user chose **audit-only**.

## Completion report (brief)

When finishing, state:

- **Scope** used (full / Go / web / docs-and-rules-only / audit-only).
- **Rules** that drove changes (by number or name).
- **Verification** command(s) run and pass/fail.
- **Commits / push**: hashes or branch update, or “none (clean / audit-only).”
